<subSubSection id="C3146527FFCDE53E50988361617EF815" pageId="12" pageNumber="129" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFCDE53E50988361611DFAB5" blockId="12.[189,794,1129,1665]" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFCDE53E509883616234FB35" bold="true" box="[189,319,1129,1153]" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Description</emphasis>
: Body length 7.0– 
<quantity id="4CF69B49FFCDE53E52368361616DFB35" box="[531,614,1129,1153]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4CF69B49FFCDE53E51258381628AFB15" box="[256,385,1161,1185]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.45" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="3.45" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.6 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: body completely black, except for the reddish to dark-brown tarsi, the reddish apical maxillary palpomere, and sometimes the dark reddish-brown antennomere XI.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFCDE53E50988201625CFA75" blockId="12.[189,794,1129,1665]" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">
Elytra with punctation not subject to sexual dimorphism, dense, but near scutellum not extremely dense (similar to the condition in female 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFCDE53E519382426124FAD5" baseAuthorityName="CHAMPION" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[438,559,1353,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pindarae">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFCDE53E519382426124FAD5" box="[438,559,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Z. pindarae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Abdominal segment VII on whole surface with sparse non-setiferous micropunctation. Other external characters (
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFCDE53E5241828161FEFA15" box="[612,757,1417,1441]" captionStart="Figs 260–277" captionStartId="63.[151,191,1987,2009]" captionTargetBox="[157,1395,232,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-126@63.[151,1398,232,1971]" captionText="Figs 260–277: Zyras morulus (260–265), Z. variolatus (266–270), Z. montanus (271–275), and Z. preangeranus from Java (276–277): forebody (260); antenna (261); abdomen (262); median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (263–264, 266–267, 271–272, 276–277); paramere (265, 268, 273); male tergite VIII (269, 274); male sternite VIII (270, 275). Scale bars: 260–262: 1.0 mm; 263–277: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5888380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5888380/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Figs 260–262</figureCitation>
) as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFCDE53E50FC82A26259FA75" baseAuthorityName="CHAMPION" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[217,338,1449,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pindarae">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFCDE53E50FC82A26259FA75" box="[217,338,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Z. pindarae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFCDE53E509882C26139F9D5" blockId="12.[189,794,1129,1665]" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">
♂: shapes and chaetotaxy of tergite and sternite VIII as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFCDE53E50C482E26251F9B5" baseAuthorityName="CHAMPION" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[225,346,1513,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pindarae">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFCDE53E50C482E26251F9B5" box="[225,346,1513,1537]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Z. pindarae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; median lobe of aedeagus 0.9–1.0 mm long and shaped as in 
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFCDE53E518881016137F995" box="[429,572,1545,1569]" captionStart="Figs 260–277" captionStartId="63.[151,191,1987,2009]" captionTargetBox="[157,1395,232,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-126@63.[151,1398,232,1971]" captionText="Figs 260–277: Zyras morulus (260–265), Z. variolatus (266–270), Z. montanus (271–275), and Z. preangeranus from Java (276–277): forebody (260); antenna (261); abdomen (262); median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (263–264, 266–267, 271–272, 276–277); paramere (265, 268, 273); male tergite VIII (269, 274); male sternite VIII (270, 275). Scale bars: 260–262: 1.0 mm; 263–277: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5888380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5888380/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Figs 263–264</figureCitation>
; paramere (
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFCDE53E529E81016019F995" box="[699,786,1545,1569]" captionStart="Figs 260–277" captionStartId="63.[151,191,1987,2009]" captionTargetBox="[157,1395,232,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-126@63.[151,1398,232,1971]" captionText="Figs 260–277: Zyras morulus (260–265), Z. variolatus (266–270), Z. montanus (271–275), and Z. preangeranus from Java (276–277): forebody (260); antenna (261); abdomen (262); median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (263–264, 266–267, 271–272, 276–277); paramere (265, 268, 273); male tergite VIII (269, 274); male sternite VIII (270, 275). Scale bars: 260–262: 1.0 mm; 263–277: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5888380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5888380/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Fig. 265</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4CF69B49FFCDE53E509881216204F9F5" box="[189,271,1577,1601]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
long, much longer than median lobe, and with rather long and slender apical lobe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFCDE53E50988162619EF935" blockId="12.[189,794,1129,1665]" box="[189,661,1641,1665]" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">
♀: tergite and sternite VIII as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFCDE53E52328162619BF935" baseAuthorityName="CHAMPION" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[535,656,1641,1665]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pindarae">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFCDE53E52328162619BF935" box="[535,656,1641,1665]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Z. pindarae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFCDE53E509881A1617EF815" blockId="12.[189,794,1705,1953]" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFCDE53E509881A1629DF975" bold="true" box="[189,406,1705,1729]" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Comparative notes</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFCDE53E518E81A26140F975" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2017" box="[427,587,1705,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morulus">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFCDE53E518E81A26140F975" box="[427,587,1705,1729]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Zyras morulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily distinguished from the highly similar and evidently closely related 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFCDE53E512B81E2628CF8B5" baseAuthorityName="CHAMPION" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[270,391,1769,1793]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pindarae">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFCDE53E512B81E2628CF8B5" box="[270,391,1769,1793]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Z. pindarae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
particularly by black tibiae, different punctation of the male elytra and of the abdominal tergite VII, by a basally much broader ventral process of the aedeagus (ventral view), and (both absolutely and relatively) distinctly longer parameres with a longer and more slender apical lobe of the paramere.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3146527FFCDE53E509880C167EDFEF5" pageId="12" pageNumber="129" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFCDE53E509880C167EDFEF5" blockId="12.[189,794,1993,2082]" lastBlockId="12.[831,1436,233,321]" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFCDE53E509880C16126F855" bold="true" box="[189,557,1993,2017]" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Distribution and natural history</emphasis>
: The 
<typeStatus id="54B5880EFFCDE53E525780C261ABF856" box="[626,672,1994,2018]" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected in four localities in the 
<collectingRegion id="49CAF84EFFCDE53E525180E161ECF7B5" box="[628,743,2025,2049]" country="Nepal" name="Dhawalagiri" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Dhaulagiri</collectingRegion>
and Annapurna ranges (
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFCDE53E51BF8F0162E9F795" box="[410,482,2057,2081]" captionStart="Map 4" captionStartId="65.[154,199,794,815]" captionTargetBox="[151,1398,230,785]" captionTargetId="figure-63@65.[151,1398,230,785]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="Map 4: Revised distributions of Zyras condignus (black circles) and Z. morulus (white circles) in the Himalaya." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742401/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="129">Map 4</figureCitation>
). The species appears to be confined to high-altitude habitats; the elevations range from approximately 3300 to above 
<quantity id="4CF69B49FFCDE53E54E38601661CFE95" box="[1222,1303,265,289]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="12" pageNumber="129" unit="m" value="4100.0">4100 m</quantity>
. One specimen collected in June is slightly teneral.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
